Apart from the characteristics recorded iu the diagnosis respecting the seventh pair of peraeopoda and the relation of the uropoda, the differences between the two species seem to be very small, or at least are not easily appreciated owing to the vague description given by STREETS of his species, and to the want of drawings. The characteristics recorded above are however sufficient for the distinction of the two species.

For particulars on Calainorhynchus rigidus I refer the reader to the original description and drawings given by STEBBING.
